    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1959-12-11T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1959-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="478"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                <head>478. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission at the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d478fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 320.5701/12–1159. Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1959-12-11T00:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1959—midnight</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DELGA1">Delga</gloss> 689. Re: Outer Space. <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV2">Kuznetsov</persName> called on <persName
                        corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> this morning. After certain amount of
                    preliminary bantering about possible shifts in US position and after <persName
                        corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> pressed <persName corresp="#p_KVV2"
                        >Kuznetsov</persName> to accept Lebanon, latter expressed agreement on
                    Lebanon as 5th neutral. Regarding amendment on conference participation, which
                        <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> repeated we must have,
                        <persName corresp="#p_KVV2">Kuznetsov</persName> said that he would speak
                    against it and vote against it but if amendment adopted, <gloss
                        target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> would nevertheless vote for <gloss
                        target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> and participate in <gloss target="#t_COMITE1"
                        >comite</gloss>. Russians produced typewritten text, including names of
                    countries which we checked together.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> expressed his pleasure at results
                    of negotiations which he hoped augured well for future cooperation between US in
                    outer space field as well as in other areas.</p>
                <pb facs="0950" n="920" xml:id="pg_920"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> then reviewed cosponsorship to
                    which we had previously agreed and suggested addition of Japan. <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV2">Kuznetsov</persName> agreed and proposed Romania also be
                    added. <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> agreed. We told <persName
                        corresp="#p_KVV2">Kuznetsov</persName> we would wish to inform our group of
                    results of our discussions and would then be prepared to submit <gloss
                        target="#t_RES1">res</gloss> early in afternoon. (This mtg reported <gloss
                        target="#t_DELGA1">Delga</gloss> 690.<note n="2" xml:id="d478fn2">Dated
                        December 11 (midnight). (<hi rend="italic">Ibid</hi>.)</note>)</p>
                <p>Res submitted to Secretariat immediately after lunch.<note n="3" xml:id="d478fn3"
                        >For text of the two-part resolution (1472A and B (XIV)), adopted
                        unanimously by the General Assembly on December 12, see <hi rend="italic"
                            >American Foreign Policy: Current Documents, 1959</hi>, pp.
                        1396–1397.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
